Tips:

1. A binary-based palindrome has to be odd, since you can't count leading zeros.

2. Palindromes == Symetric, for decimal-base palindrome:
	6 digits: 999,999  --> 5 X 10 X 10
    5 digits:  99,999  --> 5 x 10 x 10
    4 digits:   9,999  --> 5 x 10
    3 digits:     999  --> 5 x 10
    2 digits:      99  --> 5
    1 digit:        9  --> 5
    ------------------------------------
    Total:             --> 1110
  
	thus, we only need to test if the 1110 decimal palindromes are also binary palindromes
